(Jung Yi-hyun!)

22
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:05,200
(I played Little League too,
so I know how you feel.)

23
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,840
(So come down. Let's talk here.)

24
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,600
Just talk from there.

25
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,560
-What is he saying?
-I don't know.

26
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,920
Then give him a megaphone too. Darn it.

27
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:17,840
Hey. I'll come up, so wait a minute.

28
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,800
(Independent study)
Hey. I'll come up, so wait a minute.

29
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:20,040
Hey. I'll come up, so wait a minute.

30
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,120
(Let's talk up there.)

31
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,320
Where's the staircase?

32
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,070
Why won't he come down?

33
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:32,120
(Seyang High School)
Why won't he come down?

34
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,960
(Seyang High School)

35
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:33,840
(Seyang High School)
Focus.

36
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,520
Focus.

37
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:38,680
Focus, and you won't hear
a bomb explode next to you.

38
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,720
Why aren't we leaving? Class is over,

39
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,840
and we can't concentrate anyway.

40
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:43,040
(Independent study)

41
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:44,280
(Independent study)
Do you think Yi-hyun would like it

42
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:44,360
(Independent study)

43
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,800
(Independent study)
if all of you pour out right now?

44
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:46,000
(Independent study)

45
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,720
He's psychologically frail as is.

46
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,640
What if he jumps off impulsively
when he sees you?

47
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:55,040
I'm sure you'll be able to concentrate
very well at home then.

48
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:57,320
You'll let us go if he comes down, right?

49
00:02:58,200 --> 00:03:00,440
Yes, I'll let you go immediately.

50
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,280
The police are talking to him now,

51
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:05,120
so don't aggravate me. Just take a nap.

52
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,560
You must be tired. You've been in school
longer than other kids.

53
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:11,480
I'm going to the bathroom.

54
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,000
Hey. I said not to aggravate me...

55
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,960
Fine. As long as you're quiet.

56
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,480
Everyone focus.

57
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,640
Focus on your books.
A bomb is about to fall.

58
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:23,040
Gosh.

59
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:28,360
Hey! I'll get you fully rehabilitated.
I give you my word.

60
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:31,520
If not, I'll make sure
you can become a cop.

61
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,920
So trust me and let's go down.

62
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:35,640
I don't want to be a cop.

63
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,960
Okay!

64
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,360
I'm a friend.
They said to go up and help talk to him.

65
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:46,800
Let's talk here.
I won't go there, so don't worry.

66
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,880
Calm down.

67
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,600
Sae-bom?

68
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,400
Hey, you!

69
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,400
Hey!

70
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:59,840
Hey, kid! What... Hey!

71
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,520
Who are you? Are you his girlfriend?

72
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:03,480
No.

73
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:05,960
Hey, we can't go home because of you.

74
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:09,240
Mister, I'll talk to him,
so wait right there.

75
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,720
What's wrong with the kids at this school?

76
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:15,000
(Seyang High School)

77
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,280
Is it too hard not playing baseball?

78
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:21,200
That's not it.

79
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,680
I came up for some air,

80
00:04:23,760 --> 00:04:26,880
and suddenly cops
and ambulances showed up.

81
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,920
Who called them?

82
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,240
I'm watching to see how far they go.

83
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,680
I have nothing to do anyway.

84
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,280
There's nothing to do other than baseball?

85
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,480
Of course, not.
It was all I did my whole life.

86
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,280
I was pretty good too.

87
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,960
But look what happened to me.
How could I be okay?

88
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,880
I've done nothing my whole life,
and I was fine.

89
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:50,150
It's better if you did nothing.

90
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:52,400
I've been in a hospital for a while,
so I know.

91
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,400
It'll all become memories once they pass.

92
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:58,280
I can't play baseball ever again.

93
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:00,040
My life is over.

94
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,640
I don't know what to do...

95
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:09,280
What about you? What are you going to do?

96
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,200
Last week, it was a nurse.

97
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:13,760
Now, I'm thinking civil servant.

98
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:16,120
I need a steady income
so that I can move out,

99
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,880
but I keep changing my mind.

100
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,960
See? You're down too

101
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,520
about falling behind two years.

102
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:22,840
No, I'm not.

103
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:27,080
I'm saying our future is boundless.

104
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:32,200
It's okay, so just do it.

105
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,320
If you fail, so be it.

106
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,080
Gosh.

107
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,400
Like me.

108
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,120
What?

109
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,520
What happened?

110
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,640
Get him.

111
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,160
Hey, kid.

112
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,040
Hey.

113
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,400
Don't get me wrong.

114
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,440
It was intentional.

115
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:37,800
I pushed him onto the cushion.

116
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,150
Let's talk at the station.

117
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,680
-Wait.
-Hey.

118
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,640
Yi-hyun.

119
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:07,120
Tell him you don't want me to be punished.

120
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:09,120
He wants to arrest me.

121
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,200
Hey, Sae-bom.

122
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,040
Want to go out?

