132
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,520
He has a collapsed lung.

133
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,150
The bullet pierced the lung,
releasing the air inside...

134
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,600
Don't diagnose him, treat him!

135
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,030
(Trainee Lee Jong-tae)

136
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,280
Should I really do it?

137
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,200
Don't think. Just do as you learned.

138
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,760
Sir.

139
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,240
Sir.

140
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,800
You'll break my ribs.

141
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:27,720
Sir.

142
00:09:40,680 --> 00:09:43,040
That's my clavicle, you punk.

143
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,000
Trainee Lee Jong-tae.

144
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,720
You just killed a team member.

145
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,040
TMP point deduction.

146
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,160
(Tactical Medical Practitioner training)
TMP point deduction.

147
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,560
(Tactical Medical Practitioner training)

148
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,400
(TMP score)

149
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:08,880
Your acting was good.

150
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,480
-Was it?
-Yes.

151
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:15,680
Put your gloves on.

152
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,040
That way, he won't slip.

153
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,840
What are you doing?

154
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,560
-Will you really deduct points?
-Yes.

155
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,520
He was slow to make decisions and fearful.

156
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:26,560
If you're the standard,

157
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:28,920
everyone in this world would fail.

158
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:30,200
(Trainee Yoon Sae-bom)

159
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,520
-SWAT!
-SWAT!

160
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:48,440
Here.

161
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,320
He has a bullet wound and can't breathe.

162
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,880
What must you do?

163
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,520
(Trainee Yoon Sae-bom)

164
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,040
So...

165
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,480
Wait!

166
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,080
Yoon Sae-bom!

167
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:01,360
What are you doing?

168
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:04,560
They started using this because of you.

169
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:08,040
Because you stabbed him in the chest.

170
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,440
And he ended up being transferred
to a patrol station.

171
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,680
I heard from him recently. He said
the patrol station was a perfect fit.

172
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:16,800
Really?

173
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,880
He even sent me a gift card.

174
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,080
What about me?

175
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,400
Why didn't he send me one?

176
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,600
He must have had his reasons.

177
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:27,320
I'm starving.

178
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:28,720
Let's go eat.

179
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:35,600
(Motel)

180
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,320
Front desk.

181
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,600
I hear it too.

182
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,520
The second floor?

183
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:58,760
Okay, I'll tell them.

184
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:04,520
What are they doing
in the middle of the day?

185
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,040
Sir.

186
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:20,960
If you break anything,
you'll have to pay for it.

187
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:30,360
Do you want to get beat up?

188
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:46,480
(The days are getting slightly warm,)

189
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,840
(but the fact that we can breathe
without wearing masks)

190
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:51,480
(makes it a happy day.)

191
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,800
(Although the world has changed
since before the Covid-19 pandemic,)

192
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:58,400
(we've learned to appreciate
average days.)

193
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:00,240
(I hope)

194
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:03,160
(you all have a happy afternoon)

195
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:06,280
(during which you can see
each other's faces and smiles)

196
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,760
(and look up at the blue sky
and take deep breaths.)

197
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:12,520
(Enjoy the rest of your day.)

198
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,760
(I'll be back tomorrow...)

199
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:17,680
(We never know
when there will be another epidemic.)

200
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:25,560
(Jung Yi-hyun)

201
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:29,080
(Jung Yi-hyun)

202
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,040
(Jung Yi-hyun)
Here.

203
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:30,120
Here.

204
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:32,720
Do you still want to play baseball
with your bum knee?

205
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:35,120
They pay me if you play as a ringer.

206
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,040
-What's the case?
-A murder.

207
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,320
You didn't even know that?

208
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,720
I came because I was told to.

209
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,480
I even gave up my day off
and a baseball game.

210
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:45,520
-You should be grateful.
-Ever so grateful.

211
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:46,760
-Here.
-Babe.

212
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,960
The next room reported it.

213
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,160
-When we came out...
-Excuse me.

214
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,280
-Who's the victim?
-The clerk.

215
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,120
Let's go.

216
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,400
-And then...
-What is going on here?

217
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,640
What did he do to his neck?

218
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:29,840
I don't know.

219
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,080
It looks like it was a blunt knife.

220
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,080
Maybe to make it hurt?

221
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,600
Who's the suspect?

222
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:36,960
The one staying in this room.

223
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:39,280
People complained like crazy
because he was so loud.

224
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,320
Who covered him up?

225
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,040
Did you cover him up?

226
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,600
No, sir. That was how we found him.

227
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,640
-Any witnesses?
-Not yet.

228
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,520
They found him like this.

229
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,120
Did they check the security videos?

230
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,520
The security...

231
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:03,640
Why you...

232
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,920
What about the security videos?

233
00:15:09,680 --> 00:15:11,280
They're checking them now,

234
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:13,720
but they don't have any footage
of the suspect leaving.

235
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,280
He covered the dead
before fleeing the scene.

236
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,240
But he wasn't caught leaving on camera.

237
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:25,200
He must've filled out an entry form.

238
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:27,360
But we won't get access, I'm sure.

239
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,440
Since it's a violation of privacy laws.

240
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:31,520
Murderers don't have rights.

241
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,840
We should round them all up
and send them to prison.

242
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,640
I just don't get it.

243
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,880
Not you.

244
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,240
What?

245
00:15:48,320 --> 00:15:49,640
I assume they didn't look in here.

246
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,840
(Jung Yi-hyun)

247
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:08,240
Hey, I know you're the type to drill
into the investigation with pure luck--

248
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:10,240
I'm not.

249
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:14,480
Someone I know is way more...

250
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,160
Sir.

251
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,480
Come out.

252
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,880
Are you joking around?

253
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:26,120
You're dead meat if you are.

254
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,640
Darn it.

255
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,320
I looked him in the eyes.

256
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,520
Hey, we caught the criminal.
So don't come in.

257
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,320
Come in later.

258
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,960
(Resident ID Card, Sung Woo-je)

259
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:50,600
Did you do it, Mr. Sung Woo-je?

260
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,360
I don't know.

261
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:57,440
Did you cover the body
because you were scared to look at it?

262
00:16:58,720 --> 00:16:59,920
But why did you kill him?

263
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,840
You can't remember that either?

264
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,080
I think I had a dream.

265
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,080
Was that dream about killing him?

266
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,600
Covered in blood like this,
you weren't able to run away anywhere.

267
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:19,040
And the police barged in
when you weren't in your right mind.

